c rationalization for public education. First of all, not all parents who send their kids to private school are wealthy. An awful lot of them make major sacrifices to &quot;invest&quot; in their child rather than empty, leftist rhetoric. The assumption that all people who send their kids to private school are wealthy should be a clue there is an agenda here. If that's not clear enough, how about this: “There are a lot of reasons why bad people send their kids to private school,” Benedikt wrote. I didn't know I was bad to sacrifice for my child's education until she pointed it out to me. Thanks. There is no doubt that this is an obvious attempt to say we need to downgrade everyone's education so everyone will be equally uneducated. It has already been done to public education and that is why people sacrifice to send their children to private school. This is just another case of self justification for class warfare from another bed-wetting liberal. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1248" language="en" documentId="3927" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="AlfredENewman52" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:13PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="19" thumbsDown="0" origId="3927" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1248"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>